* [When Helping Hurts: How to Alleviate Poverty Without Hurting the Poor . . . and Yourself,](http://www.amazon.com/When-Helping-Hurts-Alleviate-Yourself/dp/0802457061) by Steve Corbett and Brian Fikker
* [A Bed for the Night: Humanitarianism in Crisis](http://www.amazon.com/A-Bed-Night-Humanitarianism-Crisis/dp/074325211X) by David Rieff
* http://halfinten.org The Campaign to Cut Poverty in Half in Ten Years
* [#2030now ](https://twitter.com/search?src=typd&q=%232030now) -the social movement of end poverty of Jim Kim : World Bank and videos week 2
* Who is Really Dependent upon Welfare, They're Wealthier Than You Think (http://www.upworthy.com/who-is-really-dependent-on-welfare-theyre-wealthier-than-you-think)
* [How The Economic Machine Works](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PHe0bXAIuk0) The best explanation of the economy that most people didn't understand.
